Definition: a substance produced by the mucosa of the stomach and intestines that is essential for the absorption of vitamin B12
Example: lack of intrinsic factor can result in pernicious anemia
Synonyms: noun, event, factor, a, substance, produced, by, the, mucosa, of, stomach, and, intestines, that, is, essential, for, absorption, vitamin, B, lack, intrinsic, can, result, in, pernicious, anemia
Category: noun.substance
